imdb.title: Pîchi gâru
imdb.plot: Momo, a high school student, is torn between two love interests, each of whom possess great qualities.

episodes.title: Rabu harikên
episodes.plot: Being the new girl at school is never easy, just ask Momo Adachi. When your 'best friend" spends most of her time trying to show you up you just can't be too careful.

episodes.title: Torappu kisu!
episodes.plot: When you finally find your true love you should want everyone to know, right? But when your 'best friend" has less than your best interests at heart, the rules are rewritten and anyone's the author.

episodes.title: Koko made yaru!? Sûpâ Sae
episodes.plot: Momo and Toji seem to have everything straightened out, but when Toji gets hospitalized, Momo finds out just how far Sae is willing to go to keep them apart.

episodes.title: Kiyoku tadashii hakyoku sengen
episodes.plot: With suddenly reformed playboy Kairi at her side, Momo attempts to set the record straight with Toji. But when her accusations are shattered by Sae's innocent act, she takes a desperate stand.

episodes.title: Shakunetsu dotô no suiei taikai
episodes.plot: Now that Sae has gotten what she wanted, you think she would leave poor Momo alone. But after spreading even more vicious rumors, she volunteers her 'friend" for the school swimming competition.

episodes.title: Gekitotsu! Koi no sadon desu
episodes.plot: With the school swim meet close at hand, Momo suits up to do her part and help Class Three, but with a plan afoot to sabotage the races, it looks as if Momo's about to take the fall.

episodes.title: Tsukanoma no LOVE sain
episodes.plot: With a plan afoot to sabotage the races and a 'secret embrace" exposed, it looks as if Momo's about to take the fall.

episodes.title: Burakku gâru
episodes.plot: With Sae and Jigoro a romantic commodity, her classmates have once more turned a blind eye to past events. True to her nature, she can't help but rub all of the perks of her new celebrity status in her old friend's face.

episodes.title: Jun'ai hakai kôsaku
episodes.plot: Toji has planned a private party for Momo's birthday that will be a night to remember, but Sae has planned a completely different 'party' of her own.

episodes.title: Pîchi kuraishisu
episodes.plot: Kairi to the rescue! Determined to teach Sae a lesson she'll never forget, Kairi convinces Sae that she's perfect for the starring role in a new movie.

episodes.title: Setsuna sugiru wakare
episodes.plot: Can Toji really love Sae? Even after seeing it with her own eyes, Momo can't believe that he would break up with her for Sae.

episodes.title: Momo no hana, saita?
episodes.plot: With the new class lists posted, Momo finds herself stuck with both Toji and Sae. She had hoped that the new year would prove a fresh start, without the daily reminder of what she has lost.

episodes.title: Shôgeki! Moto kano rannyû!?
episodes.plot: Who's that girl?!? Just when Momo finally starts to relax and enjoy the relationship that is growing with Kairi, she finds a picture of him with a mysterious girl.

episodes.title: Arashi yobu otoko
episodes.plot: Kairi continues to amaze Momo, even going out of his way for the brother whose shadow he's always had to live in.

episodes.title: Honmei wa dare?
episodes.plot: While looks can be deceiving, Momo's no stranger to deception. When she finally realizes that Kairi was telling the truth about his brother, she returns to his side of things.

episodes.title: Donzoko no koi no yukue
episodes.plot: When asked to explain his relationship with Misao, the long-lost love from his past, all Kairi can say is 'Sorry." Once again hurt and confused, Momo tries to figure out how Kairi could have lied to her

episodes.title: Jun'ai ichikusen!
episodes.plot: Momo decides that being 'second best" with Kairi is better than being without him, and they proceed to make plans for a summer vacation together.

episodes.title: Manatsu no yûwaku
episodes.plot: Feeling jilted by the kiss between Kairi and Misao, Momo doesn't really know what to think anymore. When he tries to apologize, things don't get any better.

episodes.title: Kimochi no pazuru
episodes.plot: With Kairi gone for the summer and Toji working by her side, Momo is more than a little self-conscious. Sae finally decides to delete all of the blackmail photos, setting Toji free.

episodes.title: Arashi no ichiya
episodes.plot: With Kairi and Momo on their way to rendezvous, it looks as if things might finally be resolved. But when a chance meeting between Misao and Kairi erupts into chaos, Momo is only there to see part of the story.

episodes.title: Koi no sainen chuihô
episodes.plot: As the new school year begins, the rumor mill picks up right where it left off. Momo gets everyone talking when she shows up hand-in-hand with Toji instead of Kairi.

episodes.title: Nônai ren'ai
episodes.plot: Momo discovers that Kairi has replaced Misao's picture in his student handbook with hers. Could he still have feelings for her?

episodes.title: Tsukitsukerareta sentaku
episodes.plot: With Sae's sights set on Misao, it can only mean trouble. But once Misao uncovers the truth, she decides to resolve the problem herself.

episodes.title: Sayonara no shinjitsu
episodes.plot: Crushed by Momo's decision to stay with Toji, Kairi resorts to drastic measures to make her listen to him. But Momo's mind is made up and she's had her fill of the drama.

episodes.title: Rasuto harikên
episodes.plot: As Momo and Toji leave for their day-trip, Kairi and Sae watch from a distance. When Momo receives news that Kairi might be in danger, she is forced to choose between the two once and for all.
